1
00:00:48,159 --> 00:00:48,679
Apprentice

2
00:00:51,840 --> 00:00:53,399
This place is pretty huge.

3
00:00:54,799 --> 00:00:56,320
What kind of bones are these?

4
00:00:56,520 --> 00:00:57,640
Why are they so big?

5
00:01:05,359 --> 00:01:07,159
They look like they belong to an elephant.

6
00:01:07,519 --> 00:01:09,920
They probably used elephants because it sounds like "auspicious."

7
00:01:11,359 --> 00:01:12,599
Back in the Shang dynasty,

8
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:15,840
they used ivory and elephant bones as burial objects.

9
00:01:16,079 --> 00:01:18,480
Many ivory pieces were unearthed at the Yin Ruins.

10
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:23,439
It seems the Dian King wanted his tomb

11
00:01:23,719 --> 00:01:25,480
to have a more auspicious atmosphere.

12
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:27,560
Let's go.

13
00:01:28,359 --> 00:01:28,840
Let's go.

14
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:29,959
Everyone, be careful.

15
00:01:29,959 --> 00:01:30,719
But

16
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:33,760
why are some elephant bones only half-buried?

17
00:01:34,079 --> 00:01:37,040
These bones were intentionally half-buried.

18
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:39,239
It signifies ascending with the royal carriage.

19
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:41,400
This shows that the master of this tomb

20
00:01:41,799 --> 00:01:43,359
wanted to achieve enlightenment and ascend to heaven.

21
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:47,159
For a tomb of a small southern kingdom like the ancient Dian,

22
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,640
to have such a grand scale,

23
00:01:48,959 --> 00:01:51,799
it's all because one man wanted to become an immortal after death.

24
00:01:52,079 --> 00:01:53,719
He wanted to protect his empire for ten thousand years,

25
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:56,760
making hundreds of thousands of commoners work like beasts of burden.

26
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:57,719
In the end,

27
00:01:58,439 --> 00:02:00,680
it was nothing but a pipe dream.

28
00:02:00,879 --> 00:02:01,680
Yeah.

29
00:02:01,799 --> 00:02:03,480
He can only stay in this cave,

30
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,480
rotting away with the sun and moon.

31
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:08,800
This is amazing.

32
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:10,520
Petrified wood.

33
00:02:12,199 --> 00:02:13,759
Are these all wood fossils?

34
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:14,879
Wood fossils?

35
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:17,639
This is petrified wood.

36
00:02:18,599 --> 00:02:19,240
Lao Lu,

37
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,680
how much is this stuff worth?

38
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:23,759
Get a thick one to trade for an alleyway,

39
00:02:24,439 --> 00:02:26,599
or take a small one

40
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:28,280
to buy a courtyard house.

41
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,479
Take it easy.

42
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:35,360
Anything taken from here must be handed over.

43
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:37,039
Right.

44
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,800
I meant taking a small one

45
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,479
to hand over to the organization.

46
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:42,159
How enlightened of you.

47
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,479
Historical artifacts must never be pocketed.

48
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,520
Oh, my precious.

49
00:02:50,759 --> 00:02:52,280
Don't you guys find it strange?

50
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,520
Wood fossils

51
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:55,680
usually require a very dry environment

52
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,840
to prevent them from rotting.

53
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:58,199
But this is Guyu Valley.

54
00:02:58,199 --> 00:02:59,840
It's damp everywhere.

55
00:02:59,879 --> 00:03:01,000
So I'm guessing

56
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,479
that here,

57
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,120
hundreds of millions of years before the Dian King found it,

58
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:07,680
there was violent tectonic movement.

59
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:09,800
Careful! Heads down!

60
00:03:14,719 --> 00:03:15,719
What the hell was that?

61
00:03:17,159 --> 00:03:18,479
What is this thing?

62
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,199
A bat.

63
00:03:19,199 --> 00:03:20,159
A bat?

64
00:03:22,039 --> 00:03:23,599
Bats suck blood, right?

65
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,080
With a size like that,

66
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,080
if it bites us,

67
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,280
wouldn't it suck us dry?

68
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,520
Y-Yeah, exactly.

69
00:03:28,759 --> 00:03:30,840
Fatty, that's a flying fox.

70
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,199
A flying fox?

71
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:33,520
They don't eat meat or suck blood.

72
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:35,039
They only eat plants and nectar.

73
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:38,960
You just know so much.

74
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:39,960
You just have to explain everything.

75
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:41,039
You know everything.

76
00:03:41,039 --> 00:03:42,240
Can't you leave some mystery?

77
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,560
You say that as if you weren't scared.

78
00:03:49,919 --> 00:03:50,639
Let's go.

79
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,039
Have you guys noticed?

80
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,360
Ever since we came through that secret passage,

81
00:03:56,599 --> 00:03:58,439
the deeper we go, the bigger the space gets.

82
00:03:59,439 --> 00:04:01,240
It reminds me of a legend.

83
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:03,120
It says an immortal had a gourd.

84
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,080
This gourd could hold the entire universe.

85
00:04:05,159 --> 00:04:06,800
After entering through the mouth of the gourd,

86
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,840
the deeper you go, the bigger the space gets.

87
00:04:08,919 --> 00:04:10,960
And objects become bigger and bigger.

88
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:14,960
Old Chen, grab your weapon!

89
00:04:21,959 --> 00:04:23,480
It's over there! Over there!

90
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:29,480
It's coming!

91
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,560
Did you see it?

92
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:39,680
I saw it.

93
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:40,879
Why is it gone?

94
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,360
Could it be

95
00:04:42,639 --> 00:04:44,680
that the Gold Horn King's gourd sucked it in?

96
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,079
No, no, no, stop joking.

97
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,720
I clearly saw it flying towards me.

98
00:04:49,759 --> 00:04:50,680
Yeah.

99
00:04:52,279 --> 00:04:53,079
Let me try again.

100
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,560
So disgusting.

101
00:05:27,279 --> 00:05:28,199
Oh my god.

102
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,399
It's so huge.

103
00:05:29,839 --> 00:05:31,759
It could swallow a person whole.

104
00:05:32,519 --> 00:05:34,600
This is a red-backed toad.

105
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,959
But for it to be this big,

106
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:41,040
it must be related to the radiation we discussed.

107
00:05:41,519 --> 00:05:43,959
Its skin poison glands and parotoid glands

108
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:45,480
can secrete venom.

109
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:48,439
It will spray venom once threatened.

110
00:05:48,879 --> 00:05:51,560
Then if... if we get sprayed by it,

111
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,680
what would happen?

112
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:55,600
The venom will enter through the eyes, mouth, nose,

113
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,199
or even the skin.

114
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:01,000
It causes blindness, severe pain,

115
00:06:01,079 --> 00:06:03,639
and even cardiac arrest.

116
00:06:04,759 --> 00:06:05,680
I think,

117
00:06:06,279 --> 00:06:07,680
there's no way we can get past this.

118
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:09,040
Seriously, how do we cross?

119
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:10,720
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

120
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:11,839
Don't get sprayed by it.

121
00:06:11,879 --> 00:06:12,680
Let's... let's go back.

122
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:13,680
Let's go back.

123
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,480
These toads,

124
00:06:15,839 --> 00:06:16,600
their eyes

125
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:19,199
are only sensitive to fast-moving objects.

126
00:06:20,439 --> 00:06:22,879
If we move slowly, we'll be fine, right?

127
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:23,920
You're right.

128
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:26,639
Only when it feels threatened

129
00:06:26,639 --> 00:06:28,000
will it launch an attack.

130
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,560
Are you sure

131
00:06:29,959 --> 00:06:32,920
it won't attack when it's hungry?

132
00:06:32,959 --> 00:06:34,680
Probably not.

133
00:06:44,519 --> 00:06:45,279
Look over there.

134
00:06:51,639 --> 00:06:52,439
Fatty.

135
00:06:52,519 --> 00:06:54,920
This petrified wood has been here for millions of years.

136
00:06:55,439 --> 00:06:57,279
It must be full of sand holes.

137
00:06:57,279 --> 00:07:00,079
If... if we cross, it might easily break.

138
00:07:00,439 --> 00:07:01,600
We still have to cross, don't we?

139
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:04,199
If not, we'll just be toad food.

140
00:07:04,279 --> 00:07:05,279
Let's go one by one.

141
00:07:05,519 --> 00:07:06,279
I'll go first.

142
00:07:15,959 --> 00:07:16,639
Lao Lu.

143
00:07:22,399 --> 00:07:22,959
Go.

144
00:07:34,439 --> 00:07:36,240
Lao Chen, hurry up.

145
00:07:37,879 --> 00:07:39,199
Lao Chen! Chen Youxi!

146
00:07:39,519 --> 00:07:40,199
Lao Chen!

147
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:41,560
Bro!

148
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:42,839
Lao Chen!

149
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,639
Lao Chen! Chen Youxi!

150
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:45,480
Are you okay?

151
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:47,279
Bro, are you alright?

152
00:07:47,399 --> 00:07:48,079
Lao Chen!

153
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,720
Lao Chen, how are you?

154
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,600
How are you doing?

155
00:08:56,799 --> 00:08:57,759
Fatty! Fatty!

156
00:08:57,879 --> 00:08:58,679
The rope!

157
00:08:58,799 --> 00:08:59,519
The rope, hurry!

158
00:08:59,519 --> 00:08:59,799
Okay, okay, okay.

159
00:08:59,799 --> 00:09:00,639
The rope! Lao Chen!

160
00:09:00,639 --> 00:09:01,519
Catch it!

161
00:09:12,159 --> 00:09:13,120
Hurry up, hurry up!

162
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:13,960
Go, go, go!

163
00:09:18,679 --> 00:09:20,200
Why is it so foggy?

164
00:09:20,919 --> 00:09:22,440
And it's red.

165
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:25,159
Could this fog be poisonous?

166
00:09:25,879 --> 00:09:26,919
If it were really poisonous,

167
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:28,000
we'd be dead by now.

168
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,000
We wouldn't have lasted this long.

169
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,720
What's wrong? What's wrong?

170
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:44,120
It's just a rock, and it scared you like this?

171
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,080
So jumpy.

172
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:45,960
I can't see.

173
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:50,200
I really can't see anything.

174
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,679
What is that sound?

175
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:04,200
Did you hear that?

176
00:10:10,519 --> 00:10:11,200
This... this... this...

177
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:13,240
It sounds like... like some large animal.

178
00:10:13,399 --> 00:10:14,240
A large animal?

179
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:16,960
Judging by the sound,

180
00:10:17,559 --> 00:10:18,879
its size isn't small either.

181
00:10:19,799 --> 00:10:20,600
Or,

182
00:10:20,879 --> 00:10:22,639
it's an ancient army.

183
00:10:23,919 --> 00:10:25,879
Even if terracotta warriors came out now,

184
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:28,279
they'd instantly weather into dust.

185
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:30,799
I don't care what it is.

186
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,840
Come on, everyone crouch down.

187
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:25,879
The smoke cleared.

188
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:33,519
If I call your name, dare you answer?

189
00:11:38,559 --> 00:11:41,039
It shouldn't have anything to do with the Gold and Silver Horned Kings.

190
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:42,200
Cut the crap.

191
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:44,960
Fatty.

192
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:47,840
Look over there.

193
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:49,960
Is there a hole over there?

194
00:11:50,279 --> 00:11:51,480
Looks like a toad's mouth.

195
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,240
It really is a hole.

196
00:11:56,679 --> 00:11:58,080
I guess that's the exit.

197
00:12:01,759 --> 00:12:03,679
Is that the only way we can go?

198
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:04,919
We can't go back.

199
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:05,720
Right.

200
00:12:06,399 --> 00:12:07,080
I'll go take a look.

201
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:07,720
Okay.

202
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,200
Commander Chen.

203
00:12:35,879 --> 00:12:37,120
Why are you frozen there?

204
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:56,720
Why is this place so creepy?

205
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,240
Look at that rock.

206
00:13:00,399 --> 00:13:01,360
It's full of folds.

207
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:03,039
Looks like a curtain.

208
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:03,919
Professor Lu.

209
00:13:03,919 --> 00:13:06,600
I think it looks more like a crab's lungs.

210
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:13,960
Commander Chen.

211
00:13:14,679 --> 00:13:15,600
What's the situation?

212
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:17,600
Commander Chen.

213
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,200
Why are you frozen there?

214
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:45,200
Old Chen.

215
00:13:46,279 --> 00:13:47,360
Old Chen, hurry up and run!

216
00:13:49,799 --> 00:13:50,720
Run!

217
00:14:00,879 --> 00:14:01,960
Commander Chen, over here!

218
00:14:05,399 --> 00:14:06,639
This... this thing...

219
00:14:06,639 --> 00:14:08,159
Why didn't it chase us?

220
00:14:08,159 --> 00:14:10,559
It seems to be tied up by something.

221
00:14:10,919 --> 00:14:12,519
What do you think this thing is?

222
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:14,360
Even bullets can't kill it.

223
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:15,720
Is it a bug or an animal?

224
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:16,960
It's... it's a centipede.

225
00:14:17,279 --> 00:14:18,679
Ever since we came to Nanyun...

226
00:14:18,919 --> 00:14:21,559
Why is everything we meet so huge?

227
00:14:21,639 --> 00:14:23,360
And they seem to be getting bigger.

228
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,840
This seems to be...

229
00:14:26,399 --> 00:14:27,600
the Immortal Thousand-Legged Worm.

230
00:14:31,919 --> 00:14:33,399
Aren't you a biology student?

231
00:14:33,399 --> 00:14:34,919
Why are you saying "seems to be"?

232
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:36,919
First of all,

233
00:14:37,159 --> 00:14:38,679
it's too big.

234
00:14:39,279 --> 00:14:40,080
Second,

235
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:41,279
it's wearing bronze armor.

236
00:14:41,279 --> 00:14:42,440
I can't see it clearly either.

237
00:14:42,559 --> 00:14:43,360
Third,

238
00:14:43,399 --> 00:14:45,120
I've only seen its fossils.

239
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:47,559
This kind of worm looks like a silkworm.

240
00:14:47,639 --> 00:14:49,559
It has a rare wheel-shaped neural network.

241
00:14:49,559 --> 00:14:51,080
But this worm...

242
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:52,879
It should be extinct by now.

243
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:54,240
Unless...

244
00:14:54,399 --> 00:14:56,279
Unless it's a mutated and evolved species.

245
00:14:56,679 --> 00:14:57,759
Does it have any natural predators?

246
00:14:57,919 --> 00:14:59,120
It has no natural predators.

247
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:00,639
Its neural network is highly developed.

248
00:15:00,639 --> 00:15:03,120
It can survive as long as a tiny piece remains.

249
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:04,440
Unless the oxygen level in the air...

250
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:05,559
drops drastically,

251
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:07,840
it's hard to find a way to kill it.

252
00:15:08,639 --> 00:15:09,639
You're saying this immortal worm...

253
00:15:09,639 --> 00:15:11,399
is just guarding the exit like this.

254
00:15:12,039 --> 00:15:12,919
What do we do?

255
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:15,080
We're in a tight spot now.

256
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:16,759
I don't think we can really get out.

257
00:15:16,759 --> 00:15:18,799
We're doomed. All doomed.

258
00:15:19,559 --> 00:15:21,000
Not only can we not get out,

259
00:15:21,039 --> 00:15:22,600
we can't go back either.

260
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:24,519
Wolves ahead, tigers behind.

261
00:15:24,919 --> 00:15:26,000
What are we supposed to do?
